  "text": "The abbreviation M * = M + 2 3 ∆tA for the system matrix of the SBDF2 method is used. We thus have to solve only one symmetric linear system per time step and the computational cost for this is determined by the structure of M * . This is the reason why we chose to use the SBDF class instead of, for example, the IMEX Runge-Kutta class of [CITATION_1] .",
